snippet.textDisplay: Pakistan is one of those places that just throws out amazing vocal artists. Off the top of my head Cyprus and Wales are similar. I am sure there are more. However, if you need a blast of beautiful voices you can’t go wrong with Pakistani singers. Coke studio is a gateway for westerners as you get the voices in a familiar setting. You also learn that western music is pretty boring at the moment.

snippet.textDisplay: I've been listening to this masterpiece for a decade, now more than ever, because my 10 months old daughter absolutely loves it, specially Sonu Kakkar's interlude. What I hadn't noticed, being a hobby guitarist myself, was how nuanced Nizel's electric guitar is! Not flashy, not loud, just filling up the spaces as melodically as possible, with complete ease! Brilliant use of wah pedal. ♥
